The paper discusses the implementation of DevOps principles and practices in a software development organization, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The study also explores the use of technological enablers, such as automation pipelines, which could be categorized under cybernetics (cs.CY) or distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also mentions the benefits of DevOps, such as increased deployment frequency and improved communication, which could be relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) or networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories.
